ever learned, one of the defining things about humanity.  ... that every
time somebody opens their mouth they have an opportunity to do one of two
things--connect or divide.  Some people inherently divide, and some people
inherently connect.  Connecting is the most important thing, and actually
an easy thing to do.  I try to make a connection with someone every time I
talk to them, even if I'm firing them.  Because a connection can be made.
People can be treated with respect.  That is one of the most important things
a show runner can do, is make everybody understand that we're all involved,
that we're all on the same level, on some level.  I'm shocked that there
are so many people that live to divide.  Whether it's to divide people
from each other, or from themselves--but it is a constant in everything.
